SoMa.title: MOSSO - 1 Bedroom Available in a 2 x 2 Apartment
SoMa.text: Live like a BOSS in comfort in the middle of all the action restaurants shopping near Market Street Forgive the fuzzy camera phone pictures this is an awesome apartment!    Special Note: 5th Street is extremely safe but things begin to get more interesting on 6th to 11th streets so I would recommend avoiding anything in that stretch    APARTMENT - MOSSO - 400 Building:  - Luxurious 2 bathroom modern apartment with AMAZING city views  - Great living space washer and dryer inside the apartment  - Well furnished Kitchen and hardwood floor in the common areas  - Grill and garden on the rooftop terrace beautiful amenities  - Gym aka Fitness Center and Pool Table  - Resident lounge with Free Coffee  - Free wifi aka Wi-Fi in common areas and media room  - Bike Storage and Care Center  - Non-Smoking building  - (There is also a pet care center but I do not wish to have a pet in the apartment)  - Credit check and verification of income required  - Proof of financial responsibility required  - Washer/dryer in the unit  - Parking Available $150 per month    LOCATION:  - Live in the middle of SOMA on 5th Street on the 7th Floor  - Walking distance to street shops and restaurants  - Target and Whole Foods Grocery Stores are 3 blocks away  - Walking distance to BART (5 mins) and Caltrain (15 mins) and Bus (0 mins)  - Close to Powell Street Station and Union Square  - Apple Store is a 10 min walk  - Close to Uber Twitter Eventbrite WeWork Lyft Hack Reactor School of Dentistry  - 2 minute drive to either 101 or 280  - Walking distance to Mission and Dogpatch including UCSF Mission Bay Campus  - There are several coffee houses within 3 blocks including Bluebottle    The ROOMMATE (Me):  - Indian Origin Technology Sales professional in his 30's  - Originally from Mumbai India / University of Georgia  - Love food and will experiment in the kitchen from time to time  - Respectful friendly clean and financially responsible  - Occupies the smaller bedroom with a non-private bathroom  - Looking for a working professional with similar habits    The DETAILS - MASTER BEDROOM:  - Master bedroom - Completely Private  - Unfurnished  - Private bathroom  - Available on Oct 1 but early move-in can be arranged  - Rent: $1800/month + third of utilities (about $50)  - One year lease  - Deposit: $2000    The DETAILS - CONVERTED BEDROOM / LIVING ROOM:  - Living Room converted to a bedroom Semi-Private  - Unfurnished  - Shared bathroom  - Available on Oct 1 but early move-in can be arranged  - Rent: $1400/month + third of utilities (about $50)  - Shorter Lease Possible (min 6 months)  - Deposit: $2000    REPLY WITH:  - Brief introduction (hey you can copy-paste its ok!)  - Do you like organize and clean up your space at least once a month?  - LinkedIn profile    NOTE: We would convert the living room into a third bedroom with a low partition or a roommate-on-couch situation That will help bring down the cost of living in this expensive city

SoMa.title: Great Apartment and Location
SoMa.text: Hey looking for a roommate for a great 2B/2B apartment in the Beacon starting Oct 1st  My current roommate found a deal that was too good to pass up  I've personally just moved here and looked at a lot of places and the one I'm in now is still the best I've found  So I'd like to fill the other room and keep it  I was going to put how sunny it was in the title but literally everything here is sunny    The building:   * fantastic location: easy access to Caltrain Muni Bay Bridge 280 and 101 Safeway Crossfit-Gym and views of AT T Park  *24-hour doorman  *Safeway is right downstairs Across the street from AT T ballpark   * hardwood floors in the whole apartment (no carpet) granite kitchen  * large bedrooms walk-in closets  * bedrooms are separated by the living room so there's lots of privacy   * key-fob security concierge high-end gym spa pool and other amenities    Me:  Mid 30's  Works on the peninsula at a VR startup  Quiet during the week  Learning about the city on the weekends    You:  Late 20's or 30's  Laid back no drama  Just want to live with someone I can trust  That's the biggest thing to me  Don't have to be best friends    It's really a great apartment  I'd like to show as many people as possible this Sunday Afternoon (9/11) so if you're interested please send facebook and linkedin links and tell me a little bit about yourself and we can figure out a time  Thanks!

SoMa.title: 1BR in a 2BR/1BA, $2250 Bridgeview Luxury Condo in SOMA
SoMa.text: Hi Everyone    I'm looking for a roommate to fill the other bedroom in a 2BR / 1 BA luxury condo unit (Bridgeview) in San Francisco's SOMA / South Beach neighborhood available Oct 1st     If interested please email me with a little bit about yourself and we can setup a time to chat / tour the apartment!    Rent: $2250 (includes water and garbage)  Available: Oct 1st (date is negotiable)  Term: 12 months  Everything is furnished except for your bedroom Split internet and cable    About the building:  - High-rise luxury condo building : The Bridgeview located at 400 Beale St  - 24-hour guard doorman and concierge services  - Secured key-fob entry to the building elevators and parking garage  - Gym lap pool hot tub  - Roof-top area/sun deck with barbecue grills lounge chairs and tables - with spectacular views of the Bay Bridge  - Plenty of permit street parking in front of the building - or parking spaces available in the Bridgeview garage for $250/month    About the unit and room:  - Spacious floor plan with hardwood floors maple cabinetry granite counter-tops stainless steel appliances (includes dishwasher)  - In-unit washer/dryer    Area and Access:  - 2 blocks from the Embarcadero waterfront and Rincon Park - great for walks or runs along the Bay  - 10 - 15 min walk to the Ferry Building - awesome Saturday morning Farmers Market!  - 8 min walk to AT T Ballpark  - Quick bike ride / 20 minute walk to Caltrain Station @ 4th/King  - Easy walking access to Downtown Market Street Union Square  - 3 blocks from the MUNI line / 4 blocks to BART  - Walking distance to fabulous bars/restaurants: 21st Amendment Prospect Town Hall Lord George Waterbar    About me:  - 25 y/o male  - Data Scientist at large tech company    About you:  - Respectful clean (I'm bit of a neat freak) friendly and responsible  - 20s - 30s female or male  - Non-smoker  - Good credit (will need to pass credit check + pay stubs/references)

SoMa.title: $2400 Private BR/BA in Luxury 2-BR Apt in 100 Van Ness Building
SoMa.text: Hello    I moved to the Bay last year from Detroit I have lived in the 100 Van Ness Building and I am moving to larger unit in the building The apt is 1100 SQFT and has 2 bedrooms and 2 bathrooms The Apartment is fully furnished except for your bedroom    About me: I work in Marketing down in the Financial District and I travel often for work I am 29 years old super clean and have a maid twice a month I am very low key and have friends over for dinner once or twice a week I am very easy going and prefer you be as well I can't allow any pets in the building Send an email if you are seriously interested and attach a copy of your LinkedIn URL and a little bit about yourself    I am attaching pictures of my current unit the new Apt will be the same just 400 SQFT bigger The price for the second room is $2400 plus utilities Check out the site for more info www100vannesscom

SoMa.title: 2B2B room available
SoMa.text: Hi my roommate is moving out and I need someone who can enter the lease for 12 months    I am software developer and a nerd I am looking for someone that's really clean organized and respectful of shared spaces    The building has a gym a free office space cafeteria ping pong tables patio with grills and a fireplace Bart/Muni is a block away The apartment is new and modern Internet 160mb down dishwasher laundry and dryer in the apt trash and recycle on floor (in front of the apt) There is a secure bike storage where you can park your bike and a bike tools corner as well    The living room furniture is instead already paid for    Move in date September 1st please include social profiles in your message to schedule a viewing thanks!    http://wwwavaloncommunitiescom/california/san-francisco-apartments/ava-55-ninth

Russian Hill.text: - $1100 / 70ftÃ‚Â² - Very Small Bedroom in Large Nice Russian Hill Apt (Russian hill)    70ft2  The Room: We have a small room available in our large lovely Russian hill apt The room is ~10x7 ft with a deep closet two windows nice hardwood flooring and great lighting The room is small so you are welcome to take advantage of the very large communal living space The room is partially furnished with a full size loft bed The rest of the house is fully furnished    The Apartment: Large Edwardian style flat with all hardwood flooring and tile Updated kitchen with dishwasher and garbage disposal We have our own washer and dryer in a room just off the kitchen Large living room and family room with bay windows One full bathroom and another half bath Lots of built-in storage space We also have an adorable little yorkie (hypoallergenic) As much as we love pets we only have room for one We have an cleaning person who cleans the apartment every two weeks so the place is always clean Street parking only    About Us: Two females: 26 and 34 We both work 9-4 jobs during the week We are pretty calm during the week and like the place relatively quiet but we really enjoy hanging out with each other too During the weekend we are out to dinner shows drinks hiking yoga and enjoying the city We are definitely past our party days   sometimes we can be out late but we don't bring the party home   and would like to keep it that way :) We do have the occasional dinner party or game night We are clean and respectful We are friends but have our separate lives as well     About You: We're open to a male or female in their * late 20's to 30's who is clean and respectful Someone who is done with smoking drug and partying daysWe welcome boyfriends/girlfriends but not as an additional roommate     Rent: $1100/month utilities not included plus deposit/one month's rent Rent is month-to-month but we would like to find someone who wants to stay for a while  Move in date Oct 15th

Russian Hill.text: This is a real find! Russian Hill.title: Sunny bedroom with Coit Tower views
Russian Hill.text: This room is available October 1st      I am a female in my 30s looking for a roommate to share my 1200 sq ft 2 bedroom apartment I've been in this residence in Russian hill/ Fisherman's wharf for 5 years so the flat is fully furnished and has hardwood floors throughout  The bathroom is split this offers a separate room for our shower and sink  The room is fairly large with East facing windows with a view of Coit Tower Room includes a spacious closet as well as a full wall of built in shelving   The rate is $1800 which includes all utilities as well as Comcast (Internet and cable) The only other expense would be a housekeeper that would be once every 6-8 weeks which is around $50 I am hardworking   like to keep things tidy and having the periodical visit of a housekeeper comes in handy to take care of the things nobody enjoys doing in shared spaces In the past I have allowed for a year agreement with a touch base at the 6 month mark to make sure all parties are comfortable   Looking forward to hearing from you!  Thanks!!

Russian Hill.title: Polk St Gem! 1 Bedroom available in a 2 bd apartment
Russian Hill.text: Hi     My current roommate is leaving at the end of September and I am looking for a female to take over her room and lease   This apartment is a hidden gem in Russian Hill: steps away from Polk Street with immediate access to restaurants bars coffee shops boutiques   The apartment is on the 4th floor has a ton of light (big window in the living room) as it faces the back of a house with a lot of trees     About the apt:  -2BR/1BA  -Beautiful large windows/skylight  - Recently renovated (new flooring light fixtures and cabinetry)   - Parking spot in secured garage ($300 per month)  - Laundry in building  - Elevator  - Dishwasher/Microwave   - Utilities not included: electric and cable/internet  - Lease expires 6/30/17  - Rent controlled   - NO short-term sublets  - Big bedroom comes unfurnished (151sq ft) -- fits king bed and full size dresser   - Additional storage in garage (free)     About ME:     I am a 29 year old female originally from France and moved to the US 5 years ago for my MBA and job opportunities  I work in the food tech industry as a Merchandising Analytics Manager enjoy good food and wine like politics/economy travelling and meeting people from different cultures   I work from 8-6pm travel every other month for work I am new to the city so on my free time I like exploring SF trying out new places and restaurants I am also pretty active and enjoy the outdoors (running hiking camping)     About YOU:  - Female only  - Ages 25-35  - Clean   - Career oriented  - Enjoys good conversation fun to hang out with :)    If interested please respond to this email with some information about yourself as well as a link to Facebook or LinkedIn    Thanks and happy apartment hunting!!

Russian Hill.title: 2 bedrooms available in Russian Hill Aprtmt
Russian Hill.text: Unfortunately my wonderful roommates are moving out of SF next month (one to NYC and the other moving in w her Boyfriend) but luckily for you lovely people of craigslist there are 2 bedrooms opening up next month We have an awesome spot on the corner of Polk   Greenwich We are super close to all that polk/union/and chestnut has to offer Our aprtmt is 3 bdrm 15 bath with washer dryer in unit brand new kitchen/appliances large living area and remodeled bathrooms We have been in this aprtmt for the last two+ years and absolutely adore the location      The rooms available are the mid-sized and master bedroom The rent per month is 1800 and 2000 respectively +utilities which usually comes out to about 50 a month for cable and Pg E     I'm a F in my mid 20's former accountant that just spent the last 3 months backpacking SE asia Looking for someone who is "value added" to our humble abode     I'm hoping to meet with people in the coming weeks so we can get someone in by Oct 15 to take over the spots Looking forward to hearing from ya and happy hunting!
